    "body": "Yes, that would be better still.\n\nIdeally, unescaped non-ASCII code points should be disallowed, and ASCII bytes could be represented with `\\xFF` escapes (this matches Python 3 byte string literals). But this may require having the tokenizer record more data than is otherwise required. At this point, the effort might be better spent adding full byte literals: https://github.com/rust-lang/rfcs/pull/69\n",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
