    "updated_at": "2014-11-06T18:52:19Z",
    "body": "Responding to https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/18702#issuecomment-62019605 and https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/18702#issuecomment-62019850:\n\n@mahkoh, as the person who filed it, I can assure you this bug not about the \\xHH syntax and is not fixed by #18504. As the title says, it\u2019s about arbitrarily encoding to UTF-8 for a feature that is used in context where text is not necessarily in UTF-8. I argue that what you call the expected behavior is wrong, for reasons explained above. That C is doing it wrong is not a reason for us to do the same.\n",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
